From: "copilot-swe-agent[bot]" <198982749+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 28 Apr 2026 15:18:37 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add dedicated thread method for video sending rate control

This backports PR #4332 to PJSIP 2.7.2:
- Add PJMEDIA_VID_STREAM_RC_SEND_THREAD enum to vid_stream.h
- Implement sending thread with rate control in vid_stream.c
- Change default rate control method from SIMPLE_BLOCKING to SEND_THREAD
- Add send manager and send stream structures for packet queuing
- Update put_frame() to use send thread when configured

The sending thread provides better video latency than simple blocking
by using more accurate bitrate calculation and avoiding blocking the
capture thread.

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>

Co-authored-by: trengginas <1152373+trengginas@users.noreply.github.com>
